about.description: PyXDG is a python library to access freedesktop.org standards
about.summary: PyXDG contains implementations of freedesktop.org standards in python.

name: pyxdg
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pyxdg" %}
{% set version = "0.26" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: fe2928d3f532ed32b39c32a482b54136fe766d19936afc96c8f00645f9da1a06

build:
  number: 0
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .
  noarch: python

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - xdg

about:
  home: http://freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/pyxdg
  license: GNU Lesser General Public v2 (LGPLv2)
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file: 'COPYING'
  summary: PyXDG contains implementations of freedesktop.org standards in python.
  description: "PyXDG is a python library to access freedesktop.org standards"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - marcelotrevisani
